JK Tyre Plans to Set Up 1,360-MW Power Plant in India, PTI Says

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-04-19T09:24:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-19/jk-tyre-plans-to-set-up-1-360-mw-power-plant-in-india-pti-says.html
JK Tyre and Industries Ltd., an
Indian tiremaker, plans to set up a 1,360-megawatts power plant
near Jhansi in the central state of  Madhya Pradesh , the Press
Trust of India reported, citing Vice-Chairman and Managing
Director Raghupati Singhania.  The company will make an initial investment of 13 billion
rupees on the venture, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai 
 akarve@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 